{
  "analysis": "The interrupted training left a 0-byte `/app/work/model_raw.bin`. We need to retrain in an observable way to avoid terminal buffering/hangs. The prepared fastText data exists at `/app/work/train.txt` and `/app/work/test.txt` with correct counts. fastText CLI is available at `/opt/fastText/fasttext`. Next, run training in the background with output logged, then check process status and log output. A moderate configuration should finish and exceed 0.62 accuracy; if too slow or too large, we can tune or quantize afterward.",
  "plan": "Remove the empty raw model files. Start fastText supervised training in the background with logging to `/app/work/train.log`, using dim=100, epoch=10, lr=1.0, wordNgrams=2, bucket=100000, minCount=1, softmax loss, and all CPUs. Then verify the process started by checking `/proc/$pid` and view the log.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "rm -f /app/work/model_raw.bin /app/work/model_raw.vec /app/work/model_raw.ftz /app/work/train.log /app/work/train.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup /opt/fastText/fasttext supervised -input /app/work/train.txt -output /app/work/model_raw -dim 100 -epoch 10 -lr 1.0 -wordNgrams 2 -bucket 100000 -minCount 1 -minn 0 -maxn 0 -loss softmax -thread $(nproc) > /app/work/train.log 2>&1 &\necho $! > /app/work/train.pid\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pid=$(cat /app/work/train.pid); echo \"pid=$pid\"; if [ -d \"/proc/$pid\" ]; then echo running; tr '\\0' ' ' < /proc/$pid/cmdline; echo; else echo not_running; fi\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "tail -30 /app/work/train.log 2>/dev/null || echo 'No train log yet'\n",
      "duration": 0.2
    }
  ]
}
